
/*
 * /*
 *  * This Hyperlambda code checks if the [epochs] argument exists and is not null. If both conditions are true, it adds the [epochs] nodes to a specific location in the payload of an HTTP POST request.
 *  * 1. [if] - Initiates a conditional statement.
 *  * 2. [and] - Combines multiple conditions that must all be true.
 *  * 3. [exists:x:@.arguments/*/epochs] - Checks if the [epochs] argument exists.
 *  * 4. [not-null:x:@.arguments/*/epochs] - Checks if the [epochs] argument is not null.
 *  * 5. [.lambda] - Executes the following block if the conditions are met.
 *  * 6. [add:x:@data.connect/*/http.post/[1,2]/*/payload] - Adds nodes to the specified location in the HTTP POST payload.
 *  * 7. [get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/epochs] - Retrieves the [epochs] nodes to be added.
 *  */
 */
if
   and
      exists:x:@.arguments/*/epochs
      not-null:x:@.arguments/*/epochs
   .lambda
      add:x:@data.connect/*/http.post/[1,2]/*/payload
         get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/epochs
